<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, this species ranges 11-13 mm in total length and 2.5-3 mm in maximum width. During the current census it has been observed mainly at night under artificial lights, however on one occasion it was found during daytime feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In nearby Hong Kong, larvae have been documented to bore into wood of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cinnamomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cinnamomum camphora" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="camphora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cinnamomum camphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Melia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melia azedarach" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azedarach">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Melia azedarach</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, L-R" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Knowledge" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="100 - 102" refId="B94" refString="Liu, L-R, 1992. Bionomics of Ceresium sinicum ornaticolle Pic and its control. Entomological Knowledge 28 (2): 100 - 102" title="Bionomics of Ceresium sinicum ornaticolle Pic and its control." volume="28" year="1992">Liu (1992)</bibRefCitation>
reported them as serious pests of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lythraceae" genus="Punica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Punica granatum" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="granatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Punica granatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Sichuan, but also more generally of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Malus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Malus domestica" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Malus domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Pyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pyrus" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ricinidae" genus="Ricinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ricinus communis" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ricinus communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
